OL,3,CCoronation Street tackles suicidal
OL,4,Cthoughts in bullying storyline
OL,6,F"We felt it was important to show the
OL,7,Fmental damage that bullying can do to
OL,8,Fpeople on the receiving end,
OL,9,Fespecially in the modern world, when
OL,10,Fchildren are faced with what can seem
OL,11,Flike inescapable cyber-bullying.
OL,13,F"The aggression doesn't stop at the
OL,14,Fschool gates but can find you in the
OL,15,Fsafety of your own home. Having said
OL,16,Fthat, it was also important that
OL,17,Facross the story as a whole, we showed
OL,18,Fsome hope for Liam and that by
OL,19,Fspeaking up, finally, he can begin the
OL,20,Fprocess of escaping his nightmare and
OL,21,Fbeginning to heal.
